CipCipPy
Twitter IR system for the TREC Microblog track.

Authors: Giacomo Berardi <giacomo.berardi@isti.cnr.it>
         Andrea Esuli <andrea.esuli@isti.cnr.it>
         Diego Marcheggiani <diego.marcheggiani@isti.cnr.it>
URL: <http://tag.isti.cnr.it/cipcippy/>
For license information, see LICENSE


#############################################################################


Installation:
In config.py define the constant ROOT_PATH with the library path (eg: /home/giacomo/projects/CipCipPy/)
Eventually add the sources path (eg: /home/giacomo/projects/CipCipPy/src) to the PYTHONPATH environment variable.


Dependencies:
    numpy
    whoosh
    sklearn
    nltk
    httplib2 (only for corpus downloading)


Packages and files:

config.py
    Global constants to configure the environment

corpus
    New corpus can be generated with the function corpus.builder, passing a list of instances of the classes in
    corpus.filters

external
    Interfaces for accessing to external resources

indexing
    Each module in this package contains a function *index* to generate an index from a plain text corpus, with documents
    until a specific date, and assigning it a name

retrieval
    Classes for searching, use the indexes by index names.

classification
    Supervised learning utilities

realtimeFilering
    Classes for real-time filtering (a TREC microblog task)

utils
    Generic classes and functions used in the library

test (not a package)
    Scripts to execute applications using the library (building indexes, searching from TREC topics, ...)

data (not a package)
    Data path contains all the data used by the library (cached data, indexes, ...)
